                      NPC Behavior: Callout Inheritable
                      =================================

Description
-----------

The callout inheritable is a generic behavior for use in behaviors that
wish to continue their behaviors while the NPC has no heart_beat; ie. 
no players are in the room with it. The callout inheritable uses the
heartbeat while it is running, and a callout while it is not.

It provides delay and chance settings. This behavior in inherited by the
wander behavior, so wandering NPCs can continue to do so while their
heartbeats are turned off.

The callout behavior inheritable is defined as CALLOUT_BEHAVIOR in
mudlib.h.

Callout Inheritable API
-----------------------

The callout inheritable requires that perform_behavior and reset both
call their respective parent functions. Look in the wander behavior
object for an example.

void set_chance(int chance)
- Set the % chance for the behavior to fire.

void set_delay(int delay)
- Sets the time in seconds between % chance checks.


